			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1148105">
									

<p>Actually, my concept of it is that you <em>do</em> realize it makes no rational sense, but it's the only way to get the idea out. Something about 4237 makes people unable to assign real words to what it does. Let's say you were immune to 4237's effects, and you dropped it. You'd say you just dropped it, and that it bounced. But for everyone else, saying &quot;it fell and bounced&quot; isn't <em>correct</em> enough to say that. 'Fell' and 'bounced' aren't right enough. It's something <em>different</em>, what it did was&#8230; um&#8230; christ, it was like, it&#8230; fuck it, it swoomed down and boingboinged. Remember, every written / typed report for 4237 has had all of its &quot;um, fuck, it's like, um&quot; stuff removed. Which is a lot.</p>
<p>Ever have a situation where you're telling someone a story, get stuck on a word, and it sorta kills the exchange because every suggestion your friend makes is wrong? That's this thing.</p>

